lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: =
#ccc;">offer a sense of specialness</a>; they fulfill a need for mystery an=
d conspiracies. Also because =E2=80=9Cyou can=E2=80=99t cheat an honest man=
=E2=80=9D: If you are running a scam, the ideal mark is someone who is up f=
or a little dishonesty, who is not going to insist on all the proper proced=
ures. Also because the victims here are never going to be that sympathetic:=
 They wanted to do some scam (one where they were the scammer), you served =
them a different scam (one where they were the victim), but what are they g=
onna do, call the police?</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The third kind of=
 scam =E2=80=94=C2=A0is it even a scam? =E2=80=94=C2=A0doesn=E2=80=99t pret=
end to be anything at all; it is just open about being exactly the sort of=
=C2=A0scam that it actually is. In <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbu=
siness.com/click/24393206.255798/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW=
9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTctMDUtMTYvaGVkZ2UtZnVuZC1wYXktYW5kLXRyYWRlci1saWVz/607f=
07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7843b024" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscop=
e" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;"> the early days of Ethereum</a> there were tons of thi=
ngs named like =E2=80=9CEthereum Pyramid Scheme=E2=80=9D or =E2=80=9CEthere=
um Ponzi Scheme.=E2=80=9D If you buy that you know what you=E2=80=99re gett=
ing! The value proposition of a Ponzi scheme is: =E2=80=9CIf you put in mon=
ey now, and other people put in money later, we will pay you a high return =
on your investment, but=C2=A0if you are the last one in you will lose all y=
our money.=E2=80=9D You can dress that proposition up in lies =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0say =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=80=99re investing in totally safe bonds at a guarante=
ed above-market return=E2=80=9D while actually doing a Ponzi =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0or you could not. You could just tell people what you=E2=80=99re doing a=
nd ask them if they want to play. Some will, because that basic Ponzi propo=
sition is sort of a fun game of musical chairs but with money. People could=
 want to play because they like a gamble, or because they think they have s=
ome edge =E2=80=94=C2=A0some special psychological insight or inside knowle=
dge or whatever that gives them an advantage in guessing when the game will=
 end and getting out in time.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I have mostly=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/24393206.255798/a=
HR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjEtMDEtMTMvZnJh=
